revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

dellNet.description: The Structure of Management Information for the Dell Networking OS.

dellNetCommon.name: dellNetCommon
dellNetCommon.description: All Dell Networking OS shared TEXTTUAL-CONVENTION definitions

dellNetMgmt.name: dellNetMgmt
dellNetMgmt.description: dellNetMgmt is the main subtree for Dell Networking OS mib development.

dellNetModules.name: dellNetModules
dellNetModules.description: dellNetModules provides a root object identifier from which MODULE-IDENTITY values may be based.

dellNetExperiment.name: dellNetExperiment
dellNetExperiment.description: dellNetExperiment provides a root object identifier from which experimental mibs may be temporarily based. mibs are typicially based here if they fall in one of two categories 1) are IETF work-in-process mibs which have not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the IANA. 2) are Dell Networking OS work-in-process which has not been assigned a permanent object identifier by the Dell Networking OS assigned number authority, typicially because the mib is not ready for deployment. NOTE WELL: support for mibs in the dellNetExperiment subtree will be deleted when a permanent object identifier assignment is made.
